oh hi 31 weeks 👶🏻👋🏼
this past week was different. I'm not gonna lie, hormones have been in full effect. by "full effect" I mean, shit is REAL. I've been up and down. feeling sad, lonely, insecure, figuring out the baby room and husband being in and out of town for work has been rough for some reason. I'm just emotional and I can admit that. it's not always a party over here.. we all have our moments and I wanna make sure I share the bad and the good because I'm honest and if someone asks me, "how are you doing?" I'm gonna be real and tell them how I'm really feeling. not give them your typical "I'm doing good 😳" answer. I tend to have no filter. (although, I do tend to be more vulgar but I tone it down on here 🙈😂) anyway, I know these feelings are temporary and it'll pass. I'm grateful for everything I'm feeling while I'm sheltering this little babe in my belly. 9 more weeks.. I can't wait for the day Aj and I get to meet him 👶🏻

RAW. BUTTERFINGER. PROTEIN. COOKIES. 💯🎉🍪👌🏼😛💪🏼🙌🏼😍😎🤗✌🏼️
these have made the last couple days a whole lot sweeter and because I ain't gonna lie, I HAVE to eat something sweet every single day. most times, I make my own because I know exactly what goes in it. I also tend to make whatever it is with good, clean, organic ingredients! the real ones.. not those gross ingredients/fillers/preservatives like guar gums, soy lecithin, corn syrup, natural flavors (WTF is that?!).. etc. point is, I'd rather make my own dessert than constantly be snacking on stuff that makes my body feel gross, bloated and gassy. so HERE IT IS.. the recipe for these little gems! DO IT 😜
1/2C @sproutedflour sprouted oats, 3/4C @essentiallivingfoods mulberries, 1 scoop @vitalproteins collagen whey, 2Tbs @epicseed chia seeds, 2Tbs @enjoylifefoods morsels, 2 scoops @vitalproteins collagen peptides, 2Tbs @artisanaorganics coconut oil, 2/3C @artisanaorganics almond butter (not oily), dash or cinnamon and pink Himalayan sea salt with @nikkiscoconutbutter cashew cookie butter drizzle!
place all ingredients in a food processor until smooth. use your hands to make these bad boys into little balls, then press down using your thumbs. once you've got about 16 cookies, drizzle it 🤓 place them in the freezer for about 45 min-1hr. and ENJOY ❤️ thank you @thefitforkfeed for the inspiration! I adore you!

sweet potato snackin bread is what’s up ☝🏽
i’m not gonna say, “omg guys, this bread is amazing blah blah blah” i’ll let y’all be the judge of it. so go on, do it.
1 small roasted sweet potato (i used japanese but any will work)
1 small spotty banana
3 organic pasture raised eggs
1/3C @georgiagrinders almond butter
1tsp @ferm.farm vanilla bean paste
2Tbs maple syrup
1/2C coconut flour
1tsp @bobsredmill baking powder
pinch of cinnamon + cardamom + pink salt
topping options: @eatingevolved chocolate, sprouted nuts, oats, nut butter.. do you!
first off, play some tunes to set the frickin mood and preheat your oven at 350. in a big bowl, use a fork to mash the sweet potato and banana. throw in the eggs, almond butter, vanilla paste, maple and mix it all up. add the rest of the ingredients and with a whisk, combine it all together. put the batter in a lined loaf pan with some @chosenfoods coconut oil and bake for 45 min or so. your house will smell incredible, slice it, don’t be stingy, serves 3 and you’ll eat it in 2 days. enjoy!

BANANA BACON BREAD with SALTY CHOCOLATE 🤤
it's ridiculous and it's comin in🔥on this perfect gloomy morning ☁️🌫☔️ on another note, i'm beyond excited for portland tomorrow. i'll be staying with the coolest frickin blogger around and will be seeing some sweet babes too (you know who you are 😘). this little getaway is just for fun. i wanted to take a break from social media for a couple days but i want you to experience pdx with me 🤷🏻‍♀️😎✌🏼so pack yo bags y'all!
okay, do it:
6Tbs. @fourthandheart vanilla bean ghee
6Tbs. @wholefoods maple syrup
1tsp. @simplyorganicfoods pure vanilla extract
4 ripe AF bananas
1/4C @thenewbarn vanilla almond milk
2C @bobsredmill paleo flour
1tsp. baking soda
1tsp. baking powder
½tsp. pink sea salt
1/2 bar @hukitchen SALTY chocolate bar
2 pieces of @buyranchdirect BAEcon👅🐷🙌🏼
preheat your oven to 350F. put the milk, oil, maple syrup, vanilla, and bananas in a @kitchenaidusa stand mixer and blend until smooth. in a large bowl combine dry ingredients. add banana mixture and combine just enough. fold in da bacon and chocolate🐷🍫pour mixture into a loaf pan. bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean (mine took 35min.) no need to wait til it cools.. take a bite 🤓

HAPPY SUNDAY 🙋🏻
I wanted to share the bump progress with you guys. I'm in my third trimester and time is just flying. pregnancy has been good to me so far. I can't complain. I'm enjoying it so much. I'm ecstatic to meet my Elliott 👶🏻 but also terrified to bring him into this crazy world. my husband and I are thrilled to be able to have (God willing) an all natural birth plan at the awesome birth center 👉🏼 @southcoastmidwifery with the help of my lovely doula @rubystocking. it's a scary thing to think about and trust me, I've heard the good and bad of this process but I wouldn't wanna have it any other way since we live a non toxic, holistic lifestyle 👫 I keep telling myself, our bodies as women are meant to bare children. so I'm sticking to that. I'm beyond flattered I get to experience this painful but rewarding journey in December. don't get it twisted.. I still freak out that I'm growing a human inside my belly. how the heck is this even possible😳? haha it's the craziest, most amazing feeling (whatever that means). sometimes I don't even feel pregnant. then I get reminded by the kicks, heavy breathing, feeling overheated, HANGRY all the time, constant bathroom breaks and the double takes of the belly in the mirror of course 😆
I'm the happiest and most comfortable in my skin I've ever been. I thank god for these feelings. my husband also makes sure he tells me the sweetest things and makes me feel so loved and secure because I wouldn't wanna do this with anyone else. our marriage comes first ☝🏼️ then baby 👶🏻 FYI *if something were to go differently with our birth plan, I'd be okay with it too as long as the babe and I are safe ☺️
I appreciate the love and support I've gotten from you guys ❤️

you know my addiction to bone broth but now that it's getting hot AF and don't wanna drink anything hot where do I get my collagen from?! @vitalproteins duh 🙌🏼 (it even has a good amount of protein for my 💪🏼😏) let's back track.. what is collagen?! - collagen is the most abundant protein in the body. it helps connective tissue to be strong and provides cushioning for various parts of the body. gelatin is delivered from collagen when collagen breaks down and it's great for people with food allergies or sensitivities; it even helps their bodies manage those foods better. this helps with leaky guts, skin and hair, joints, boosts your metabolism, strengthens nails and teeth and reduces stretch marks and cellulite 👏🏼💃🏻 babes, I have found this to be sooooo helpful for my overall health. I've been taking it every morning with my smoothies or yogurt and sweet potato bowls like you see here 👆🏼and I highly recommend it! cheers to health! HAPPY MONDAY!

sprouted adaptogenic brownie BALLS 🤤
I will forever make these for my pre/post workouts, snacks, dessert, hell.. any occasion!
1C raw sprouted nuts + seeds
(i used @bobsredmill buckwheat, sunflower seeds, hazelnuts, macadamia, cashews)
1 1/2C dates
1/2Tbs brain octane
1 scoop chocolate whey protein
1Tbs tocos
3Tbs raw cacao powder
2-3Tbs nut milk
1tsp vanilla extract
small handful of chocolate wafers
dash of himalayan pink salt
throw everything in a food processor and blend that shit up until you get a thick, sticky, delicious consistency. roll em up, freeze and try not to eat the whole damn batch. makes about 11 big ones 😎 serves ONE 🙋🏻🤷🏻‍♀️💯

i used to make my own nut milks back when i first started this account. for whatever reason i stopped cause i feel like i'm "too busy" or i can't get myself to drink it in 2-3 days. always making little excuses on why i don't make certain things. but i decided to try again.. with coconut milk. i've been on a coconut kick for a while now so why the hell not?! it's SUPER EASY and no joke, the best milk i've ever had. but that's just my opinion. try it for yourself!
4C filtered water
2C unsweetened coconut flakes (i used the brand, let's do organic)
pinch of pink salt + cinnamon
1Tbs @bulletproof brain octane
i put all of the ingredients in my @vitamix and blended on high for about a minute. i strained the milk and put it in a @weckjars 🤗

no need to be SALTY, get CHEER-Y with these salted chocolate peanut butter gems 🍪
i’ve made these before but tweaked the recipe just a little with ingredients i had on ✋🏽
make these and share them with your family and friends. they make the perfect gifts. remember, it’s the little things that matter.
things you’ll need: 1C @bobsredmill paleo baking flour (i usually use spelt or almond but paleo mix was DELISH), 1/2tsp baking powder, 1/2C @eatnuttzo peanut pro (make sure it’s nice and runny), 1/2C organic maple syrup, 1tsp vanilla extract, 4Tbs *melted @artisanaorganics coconut oil, 1/2tsp pink salt, dash of cinnamon and 1/2 chopped up @eatingevolved cashew milk bar squares (holy shit.. game changer 👌🏽).
DO: mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl, add the wet and stir until barely combined. add the chocolate and fold in the pieces. it should look a bit dusty. bake at 350 for 10 minutes. careful, you don’t wanna burn them. let them cool on a cooling rack. once they’re cool, option to drizzle with pb of choice and sprinkle with pink salt. you can’t go wrong with these bad boys. makes about 15 medium size good ones 🤓

a non traditional picadillo with a twist!
my mama used to always make it when i was a little girl. she’d make it with potatoes, zucchini and carrots. well this girl 🙋🏻 didn’t have much on hand so.. tweaked it a bit!
I used: 1lbs each of @buyranchdirect pasture raised organic turkey + grass fed bison, 1/2 chopped sweet onion, 1 green bell pepper, a bag of cauli rice (i bought mine at whole foods), 1 can of no salt diced organic tomatoes, 3 minced garlic cloves, and LOTS OF SPICES. didn’t measure, just threw in what i thought tasted good. (@simplyorganicfoods turmeric, cayenne, red chili flakes, pepper, cumin, garlic powder, chipotle powder, pink salt and oregano).
DO: throw in the garlic cloves and onion in a pan with @chosenfoods avo oil on high. i used my @staub_usa cast iron universal pan. just sayin. once the onion is clear and it smells lit, add the meat and cook til brown. throw in the cauli rice, diced bell pepper, tomatoes and mix it all up. add the spices and mix some mo’ 💃🏻 put the lid on and turn the stove to low. let it cook for about 20 minutes or so and give it a try without burning yourself. season to taste and if the veggies are a bit hard, let it cook for a little longer. i’m not a pro but my taste buds will let me know if something tastes awful or it needs more time so you be the judge 🤷🏻‍♀️😎

SPICY CHIPOTLE CASHEW CHEESE 🔥🧀
stuff is legit and i’m not gonna lie, nailed it with the flavors and texture. it tastes just like the one from @cafegratitude 💯 you know, that one i’m obsessed with..? now we can all make it at home and put it on EVERYTHANG 👌🏽
you’re welcome 🤤:
1C soaked cashews
1/2C mix of sunflower seeds + pumpkin seeds
1/2 small jalapeño without seeds
as much himalayan pink salt and chipotle powder as you’d like. didn’t measure 🤷🏻‍♀️
1/2 lemon juice
1tsp minced garlic
start with 3/4C filtered hot water and then add on if you want it creamier. throw everything in a food processor and 🌪 get ittttt. store it in a glass jar and in the fridge. it’s only lasted a solid 3 days in our home. we use it as a spread for breakfast tacos, dip for siete chips, sweet potato + carrot fries, popcorn topper.. endless possibilities 😛 hope you love it as much as we do. enjoy your tuesday friends!

these sweet potatoes are a must try. don't walk.. run and do it: peel a large sweet potato or yam and dice it up into small squares. fire up your cast iron skillet on high, throw some @fourthandheart garlic ghee and add in the 🍠. sauté with @simplyorganicfoods garlic powder, black pepper, oregano and himalayan pink salt for a few minutes then add lots of @bragglivefoods nutritional yeast. sauté some more until the sweet potatoes have a nice glaze to them. transfer the skillet into the oven and bake at 375 for.. 🤔😳 i'm gonna say 35 minutes or so. keep your eye on them and with a wooden spoon, mix the potatoes to ensure proper baking 🤤 they should be BUTTERY once they're done. these are by far my favorite! happy sunday friends!

the best cauli bites i've ever had 🙌🏼💯
make em' i dare ya 💁🏻
first you gotta lightly steam the whole cauli (i say about 7 min. or so), cut it up into pieces and dump it in your already heated and seasoned with @chosenfoods avo oil cast iron skillet on medium. lightly sauté the cauli with @fourthandheart ghee, @simplyorganicfoods curry powder, garlic powder, turmeric, black pepper and pink salt. i didn't measure anything.. just free ball it 😎😂🙊 mom joke *not* on fleek. anyway, once you've sautéed the cauli, add in a dash of apple cider vinegar, 1/4C @bonafideprovisions beef bone broth, lots of nutritional yeast, dash of cayenne, lightly mix and bake at 350 til crunchy 💥 i think i left mine in for 15 minutes or so.
give it a go! this is NO JOKE 🔥

this cookie combo DOUGH (get it 😉) peanut butter + ghee + chocolate. oh yes. i made these the other day and LOVED them so i decided to whip them up last night while the bub was asleep. oh the things us mamas do when the babes go to bed 🙋🏻💃🏻 hahah well, at least this mama! okay.. ready, set, GET!
2C @onedegreeorganics spelt flour
1tsp @bobsredmill baking soda
1C @wild_friends original PB
1C maple syrup (i used @wholefoods brand)
a pinch of himalayan pink salt
1/3C melted @fourthandheart vanilla bean ghee
🤷🏻‍♀️as much @enjoylifefoods chocolate morsels 🍫you'd like!
do it: pre heat the oven at 350. in a big bowl, combine the dry first. then add in the wet. stir until just combined. it should be a bit dusty looking. fold in the morsels and bake for about 10 minutes. easy af 👌🏼
this makes about 15 large cookies 🍪 *aka one big serving 🤷🏻‍♀️☝🏼😏drizzle more pb and
sprinkle some sea salt to give it a little more oomph 💯

HOW I SET THE TONE FOR THE DAY:
wake up in gratitude for another day of life, get out of bed, brush my teeth, walk to the kitchen to make some lemon ginger tea, sit on the couch or on my mat, stretch, move my body in complete silence and think about what i want to accomplish. that’s how i meditate.. until a little monster comes and makes alllll the noise! hahaha then i make a snack, change into my workout clothes and 💪🏽👊🏽🤘🏽i used to wake up and go straight for my phone. i’d open instagram and scroll endlessly to “catch up” on everyone’s feed but what made a difference was to focus on ME and not anyone else’s life. i made this change a few months ago and it’s something i’m sticking to!

you MUST try it for yourselves.. DO IT: 3C @onedegreeorganics spelt four, 1Tbs baking powder, 1tsp pink himalayan sea salt, 3Tbs @wholesomesweet evaporated cane juice organic sugar, 2Tbs @fourthandheart madagascar vanilla bean ghee and a whole can of @zevia cream soda! that's it!
preheat oven at 375.
place all ingredients, except the cream soda in a large bowl and whisk it REAL GOOD 🎶 add in the whole can of soda in the mix and combine just enough til you see it lumpy and thick. spread the batter evenly in a (i used coconut oil) greased loaf pan and bake for 35-40min. once it's done put it on a cooling rack and let it cool for a few minutes. i'm not gonna lie, i didn't wait 😳🙋🏻 SO GOOD! you're welcome!

FAST FOOD can be delicious and nutritious. 30 minutes is all you need and a frickin insta pot. took me a while to buy one just because i didn’t think i needed it.. jokes on me 😑
y’all ready for this? do it: turn your insta pot on, push the poultry button, set it for 30 minutes and place two frozen chicken breasts (i used @buyranchdirect pasture raised organic chicken) inside. i’m sure the chicken can be thawed in advance but i used frozen because it’s all i had on hand. throw in 1/2C each of @chosenfoods avo oil, coconut aminos and @stevespaleogoods sriracha sauce. put the lid on, lock that shiz and wait for it. as soon as it’s done you’ll see how juicy and tender the meat is. i’m seriously surprised and excited to use it for more recipes. for the cauli rice i used garlic powder, curry powder, chipotle powder, pink salt, black pepper, cumin and @fourthandheart garlic ghee. so easy and you can add it to any meal really 🤷🏻‍♀️

insecurities, we all have them. the other day i shared that i’m once again, losing my hair. i’m experiencing some hormone imbalances (postpartum shit) 🤷🏻‍♀️ and so many of you reached out and shared your struggles. it made me think..
as a community, we’re so powerful, inspiring and brave. not me, US. it’s incredible to hear your stories because we have lots in common and guess what? we’re not alone. don’t let self doubt hold you back from living your life. do you think i’m gonna stop smiling because of this little freckle in my gums? no way, i stopped being embarrassed by it years ago and practiced loving every bit of ME. sure i could probably laser it off but i’ve learned to live with it.
imperfections make us unique and give us character. there’s so much more to a person than what you see on the surface. i encourage you to share those insecurities that might be stirring in your head and let it go 👋🏼💯✨

so many favorites that i wanted to share with you from my weekly meal prep. these are my staples.. i'm sure you know this by now since i stick to what i know and love 😉
raw kale- i get three bunches a week for smoothies, salads, sautéing and kale chips.
brussels- i steam first then sauté them with garlic, bone broth and spices for extra flava!
carrots- roast at 375 for as long as you can. i like them roasted REAL WELL with curry, avo oil, paprika, oregano and pink salt.
roasted peppers- garlic, pink salt, pepper. that's it! roast at 350 for about 30 minutes. flipping them half way through.
mushrooms and broccoli- same thing ☝🏼
cauli- steam then freeze for smoothies. helps with digestion and adds thickness and nutrients to your smoothies. duh 😏
chicken- buy quality, pasture raised organic meat when possible. better to digest and flavorful af. i just roasted it with lemon, garlic, pepper and pink salt. so simple yet hella tasty.
grains- not shown. i love making sprouted brown rice and quinoa. you can add it to bowls and salads for extra fiber. using sprouted grains, legumes and nuts just makes your belly happier cause it's easier to digest 🤗

what's in my pantry? take a look 👀
I tend to be a PB hoarder 😳 don't judge me.
a lot of you ask.. where do I usually shop for groceries?- @wholefoods, @mothersmarkets, local farmers markets and @traderjoeslist
do I spend a fortune on food?- yes! but I literally only buy food (okay, and a gym membership💪🏼 because it's important to me to be strong). I'm not the type to spend money on clothes or makeup. I literally just buy expensive food 🙊🙋🏻 how do I budget?- I buy most of my produce at the farmers market since I get good deals. I always buy organic☝🏼️and when I find my favorite products on sale, I buy in bulk. that's how I budget even though it's still expensive 😉 👉🏼 it's important for me and my family to stay healthy. we put things in our bodies that are good for us. we lead a healthy lifestyle and truly love it. we're investing in our health and that just means everything to us in this world full of pesticides and toxins. yes, even if it costs us a fortune. we're blessed to be able to afford it.
read the ingredients! NOT carbs, sugars, fats, calories..etc. it's changed my life and I hope it helps yours ❤️ the less ingredients the better it is for you.
so go on and invest in YOU. because your health is more important than anything else. HAPPY SATURDAY 🤗

let's chat.. PROBIOTICS ✌🏼
friends, never in a million years did i think good health started in the gut. but it's the damn truth 💁🏻 80% of our ENTIRE immune system is located in the digestive tract. so many people with health issues don't realize that it stems from their gut! @silverfernbrand has locked it down with their product. 95% of probiotics don't make it into the intestines alive. this one has been tested and has 100% guaranteed survivability. it also contains a prebiotic to help activate the probiotic bacteria in the intestines which is awesome!
i used to have a lot of digestive issues back in my ED days and even after that with candida. it took me about a few months to restore my system by eating whole foods, quality meats, less sugar, no processed crap, fermented foods, bone broth, less stressing out (yes, stress causes MY body to go out of wack) and duh.. taking a probiotic! i tried a few and liked them but didn't really feel a difference 🤷🏻‍♀️ when

CASHEW BUTTER COOKIES feat. @hukitchen 🍫
they're thin, cashew buttery (it's totally a thing) on the inside and crunchy on the outside. i'm so into these! i usually make peanut butter cookies with this recipe but i've been all about cashew butter lately. the hu kitchen cashew butter + vanilla bean chocolate bar i added to the mix.. WHOA! made it THAT much tastier so i say, you must try these! don't forget to share with your family and friends. they'd dig them too ❤️
2C @onedegreeorganics spelt flour
1C cashew butter
1C maple syrup
1/3C @wholefoods extra virgin olive oil
1tsp @bobsredmill baking soda
2tsp @simplyorganicfoods vanilla
a pinch of himalayan pink salt (i also love to sprinkle a little on top of each cookie before baking 🤤)
1/2 hu kitchen cashew butter chocolate bar
pre heat oven to 350. pour all ingredients together in a big bowl and stir until barely combined. it should be a bit dusty. let the dough sit for a few minutes, then add 1/2 chocolate bar pieces and mix. sprinkle pink salt to each cookie before baking for about 12 minutes. makes about 20 medium sized bad boys 🍪TRY your best to not burn your tongue cause these are 🔥 get it 🙊😎

why is it so confusing to EAT HEALTHY these days?
i see and hear so many people talk about their dietary restrictions, allergies, intolerances, food freedom, etc. every person is SO different and not one lifestyle is the same. not to mention a lot of health products/organic food isn’t as accessible to lots. so how do we manage to obtain this healthy lifestyle we strive for?
everything in moderation and high quality is what has always worked for me. in this day and age, there are SO MANY rights/wrongs for how one should eat. in MY opinion, WE know how we feel when we put something in our body that makes us feel good or just plain awful. whatever that means to you.. fuel your body the best way you know how and with what’s around you.
because what you don’t eat is equally important as what you do eat. do you 💯

so here's the HEADS UP (literally) on Elliott 👶🏻
he's in breech position. meaning he's head up in my belly. we found out last monday I've fallen into the 3% of having a breech babe. Aj and I were both terrified, confused and everything in between. because I was 38 weeks, there was a sense of urgency to figure it out and come up with a different birth plan. we weren't sleeping well, our minds seemed cloudy and stress was kickin in 🙄 honestly, we were just afraid since everything else had gone so smoothly. then yesterday happened.. we met with a specialist in natural breech births and became aware that it IS possible to still have a safe and natural birth if baby is positioned correctly for this procedure. so, we've decided to go with it. a home breech birth is what we're doing (lord willing). Elliott is in "frank position" and weighs about 6lbs 3oz which is ideal for this kind of birth. I'm no longer confused or afraid. lots of questions were answered. I CAN and WILL do this. I have faith everything will go as God had planned. I'm grateful for the resources we've had. I truly believe this scare was a test to see how we'd react on decision making and becoming parents.. I have to say Aj is an incredible papa already and a huge support. I couldn't do any of this without him.
in the mean time, I'll be resting/nesting/eating all the food waiting for my birthing time. I'm more than happy to share this with you because things happen and sometimes it just doesn't go our way but we have to stay positive and create other plans that can be just as great.

hiiii 🙋🏻,
I've gotten some emails and comments regarding calories/macros/diets.. to be honest, I don't know how to count macros. calories I used to count back in the day and it just seemed overwhelming. diets?! I simply hate the word and the restrictions that come along with them. I suffered from an eating disorder for 2 1/2 years. I starved/binged/dieted like crazy. it sucked and I was miserable. I compared myself to every girl I saw. it was unhealthy. I didn't know how to get out of that head space and thought no one understood what I was going through. it was indeed a lonely place. with the help of Aj (my husband) and friends, I was able to find balance. what also helped was getting laid off from a job I hated for 7 years. I was able to have time off to relax and focus on what I was really interested in. YOGA, HEALTH, and WELL BEING. that's when it all started to change for me. I was able to see things more clearly and food was no longer an enemy. I'm not saying it's completely gone.. it's just no longer a struggle of mine and it NO longer defines who I am. I'm happy in my own skin. I don't care what people think of me nor do I compare myself to others. we're all different and I like to embrace that. I eat what I want, when I want. I do pay close attention to ingredients. realllll close 👀 and GMO's can suck it. I live an organic balanced life with my baby daddy and we love it.. but if you want that cookie (or two) go ahead and have it. don't beat yourself up about it. enjoy the little things 🍫🍪 I do 🙋🏻🙊

on the go? here's an idea for a quick "grab and get the hell out yo house" type breakfast 😎
the night before.. throw everything in a jar. all of it!
1/2C sprouted oats (a lot of you ask, why sprouted?) it's better for digestion! soaking grains kills off phytic acid, which essentially allows your body to take in alllll the benefits of iron, zinc, magnesium and other nutrients found in whole grains! my favorite brand to buy @wholefoods is by @sproutedflour ❤ i've been using it for a couple years now and love it! okay, back to the overnight oats 🙏🏼 1C @thenewbarn vanilla almond milk, 2 scoops of @vitalproteins collagen peptides (doesn't taste like anything or alters the texture but adds protein, helps heal your gut, joints and is great for skin, hair and nails), 2Tbs @navitasnaturals raw cacao powder + 1tsp cacao nibs (incredible for iron + magnesium) mamas, we need a little extra of this for our milk producing bodies! especially when breastfeeding so instead of taking a pill, add the real stuff to your oats 💃🏻, 1Tbs @salbachia chia seeds and chopped up organic strawberries ❤ put a lid on it, shake it up, put it in the fridge and in the morning when you're rushing and can't make a damn thing, grab and GET 🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️ go on! love y'all! 🙊😘

away with bub 🧒🏼❤️
i know sometimes going away with the babes can be difficult but truth is, you can do it! i’ve traveled with elliott many times, sometimes alone, with aj or family. they’ve all been different and quite the adventures. i must say, he’s a great little traveler and adapts well. we try to maintain somewhat of a schedule but sometimes, that’s not the case and it’s okay! it’s good to be flexible and figure things out as you go. it helps ME big time with leaving my expectations at the door and enjoying the moment. good or bad, i just go with the flow.
while we’re away, we like to keep bub busy like we would at home. we find playgrounds nearby, we scope out cool kid spots, the beach, hikes and kid-friendly restaurants. just as we like to enjoy our getaways, so do the babes. make it fun for the whole family and it’s 💯% more enjoyable!

whipped up more of my CBD raw balls because 420.. kidding 🤷🏻‍♀️ they’re just a staple in our home. insanely delicious, decadent, anti inflammatory and can help decrease stress + anxiety.. cool right? so many of you ask about this recipe so i wanted to share it again!
3/4C coconut flour
2C almond flour
2C sprouted macadamia + walnuts
7 large @thedatelady dates
2 scoops @vitalproteins collagen peptides
1/2Tbs CBD oil (i used @mowellens no you can’t taste it and no it won’t get you high)
1/2C melted coconut oil
1/2Tbs @ferm.farm vanilla bean paste (or extract)
dash of cinnamon + nutmeg + pink salt
throw everything in a food processor and blend to whatever consistency you’d like. add some nut milk if it’s too dry, roll em up, freeze em and turn up!

we love to snack on hard boiled eggs with hummus or @kitehillfoods so i have a dozen when i wanna get fancy or hard boiled when i'm in a rush or feelin lazy af. organic and pasture raised is best. we love @vitalfarms but you can also get quality eggs at your local farmers markets!
chicken.. i mean, no need to explain. we eat tons of meat. but it's important to find QUALITY organic pasture-raised meat. we get ours from our local farmer/butcher, @buyranchdirect cause they're legit. i don't really trust meat from stores these days 😳 do your research.
veggies! organic and local when possible. i can't get enough 😛 i wake up craving roasted veggies. the addiction is real. all i do is add my favorite spices, @chosenfoods avocado, coconut oil and with certain veggies i like them lathered in @farmtogold or @fourthandheart ghee. raw, roasted, steamed, sautéed.. whatever you'd like 😍
i usually roast at 375 til they're roasty 🤓(i made this up) what this means is, they're crunchy/burnt/realllllly well done 😎 just preference. this usually lasts about 2-3 days.
pro af tip but also common sense 😉: let your veggies COOL completely before storing them in tupperware. the heat will spoil your food. if you wanna re heat them, you can put what you'll be eating back in the oven or if you have a mini oven that works great too! i have a @kitchenaidusa that i love! or just use your cast iron skillet with a little oil and boom. it's easy af. i most of the time like my veggies cold dipped in hummus or bean dip or kitehill.. okay, okay. you get it 😜

do you drink?
i get asked this question a ton. answer is NO, i don’t. not because of calories or sugar but because i grew up with parents who’d drink on the reg. they were addicted and quite frankly, almost died from it.
growing up the smell of alcohol and smoke from cigarettes was a normal thing for me. my mom being passed out on the couch when i’d get home from school, normal. skipping school because i couldn’t get a ride, normal. having my friends tell me they saw my mom outside a liquor store drunk asking for money was probably the saddest thing i’ve ever heard. breaks my heart all over again as i’m writing this but i wanted to share because i know i’m not the only one who grew up experiencing these things.
i did go through a “party phase” for a couple months but it wasn’t crazy. half a cup of wine and i’d be like.. 😴 it’d always make me feel sleepy and trust me when i say, i’m good time without it. see why it just doesn’t interest me?
i’m not one to judge or look at anyone any different that choose to drink. we all have the choice to do what we want and i respect that completely. when i hang with my friends, i bring my own booch or tea and i never feel embarrassed or weird. IDGAF- is how i live my life! people who respect this decision of mine are the ones i wanna hang with anyway.
on an upside, my mom and dad have been sober for over 6 years. took 10+ years, lots of trips to the hospital and multiple rehab locations but god restored their lives completely. i have a great relationship with them, my mom is my best friend and elliott gets to enjoy them at their best. no drinks needed ♥️

cheers to a new year, same me 🙋🏻
i think new year resolutions can subconsciously put pressure on ourselves. some might even be unrealistic or just plain crazy like my “resolutions” 4 years ago.
i’d always set myself up for failure - binge hard til the 31st, get on a 3-5 day cleanse on the 1st to restart my system, get on the most trending diet, go to the gym 6 days a week and weigh no more than 105lbs before coachella.. WTF right? i was sick and incredibly selfish because i only cared about looking a certain way. i’d always fail, get down on myself pretty badly and go back to my ways shortly after my yo-yo dieting which would end in less than a month. hormones would be out of wack, i’d feel disgusted with myself, never felt good enough, pretty enough and even worse, judged even though no one knew what was going on inside.
my point is, new year resolutions aren’t about a “new you”. it’s about TRYING to be a BETTER version of YOURSELF. making the smallest changes in your daily life can lead to a HEALTHY LIFESTYLE LONG TERM. my intention this year is to be a better wife, mama, daughter, sister and friend. i’m going to start taking days off from social media to unplug and be fully present. also, i’m ready to start blogging. small steps and in my own time but i’ll get there. there’s nothing you can’t accomplish. prioritize and DO.
i hope you know how grateful i am for your support. i value this friendship i’ve made with you all so much and thank you for letting me have this platform. it’s hella fun, inspiring and most importantly, REAL. you are so loved friends and 1/1/2018 is just another day where we should strive to be more compassionate people. let’s show love towards each other because that’s what’s gonna make this new year better 💯✨❤️
stay safe and have yourselves a happy NYE! off to san diego we go!

as we get ready to close out 2017, let’s reflect on this past year. pretty sure we all had our good and not so good moments ya? you’re not alone. did you learn from those moments? what did you learn about yourself? what can you do to make 2018 better for you and others around you? i ask myself these questions because i constantly want to be a better me.. not just for the new year but for EVERY DAY LIVING.
my highlights this year were being able to continue to watch bub grow into a sweet little toddler, continuing to have a solid foundation with our marriage, work alongside aj on our business, creating relationships with new friends, see family come together, partner up with some of my favorite brands, teach people that real food and balance are indeed possible, YOU that continue to watch my journey and be a part of my life. my heart is so full ✨
my 😟 moments were losing it as a mama a couple times and getting down on myself for the dumbest reasons (i don’t even remember why i was bummed in those moments 🤔). another was thinking that every relationship i made in this instagram community was “real and friendly” but nah, some people are pretentious 🤷🏻‍♀️ lastly, not putting my phone down and learning to be present in the moment. it’s so easy to just virtually escape into these mini super computers that we hold in our hands.. but what are we missing?
*warning : honest af* i recently found myself unfollowing ig accounts that no longer served me, following new ones that excite and bring life to my feed. this doesn’t mean that i dislike those people. i still creep (don’t act like you don’t) there’s this unspoken rule that says, if you don’t follow me, you don’t like me and that couldn’t be further from the truth. i’m here to INSPIRE and BE INSPIRED.
excited for 2018. manifesting new hobbies, traveling, helping others in need, more dates 👫, babies, more honesty, time for prayer and sweet memories! invite that NEW, NEW 😎 now tell me about you..

these are a hit! both elliott and aj loved them too so it’s not just me that think they’re LIT! no sugar added, real ingredients, i used sprouted nuts for better digestion and ghee + coconut oil for healthy fats. i suggest you get on it 😎

yep, I frickin got it innnnn!
first day back to the gym felt incredible (minus my full boobies 🍼😩) but nonetheless it felt refreshing. I used to go to the gym as a chore or a way of negating calories and eat tons throughout the day. the past year and a half has been all about balance and loving what my body CAN do instead of what it looks like. I now go to the gym for my health and because I LOVE the way I feel doing it. I eat to nourish my body, not to look a certain way. food is my medicine. doctors can suck it 🙊
I've lost tons of weight after Elliott being born. mind you, I only gained 10lbs during my pregnancy. and yes, I understand that's super low but I ate LOTS of good whole foods that my body just burned off quickly. my midwives were aware and said as long as my babe was growing it wasn't an issue. all to say, I'm back to the gym to gain muscle and feel strong. because strong is the new skinny 💪🏼💃🏻

THIS IS 4 WEEKS POSTPARTUM 🙋🏻
I cannot believe 4 weeks have gone by. time is going by so quickly. motherhood has been nothing less than incredible. Elliott is one cool dude and I feel so blessed. but let's get to some real talk.. I'm often exhausted, covered in spit up + pee + poop + my milk + sweat, always starving, bored but busy (if that makes sense), feeling a bit stir crazy at home, missing the gym/yoga (which I'll be back at it tomorrow 💪🏼😏), and not being able to get out of the house as quickly has been a little difficult to adjust to. I'm not gonna lie, it's hard at times and I've had to ask for help when I needed it. being honest with your feelings during postpartum is a must ladies. lay it all out and be real. don't be scared of what people might think or say. because of my placenta encapsulations I'm feeling normal and so great. it's also helped with my recovery.
my body feels and almost looks back to normal but most importantly, I feel confident and strong. (okay, HANGRY too 🙊) mamas are like superheroes that no one ever talks about. our bodies shelter babies and then supply a specific milk formula for their particular needs.. I mean, cmon! that's just bad ass 😎
being a mom has taught me patience. it's also taught me selflessness and to slow down at times. I can't wait to do it all over again.. yes, I miss my big belly and I want more babies 👶🏻👶🏻👶🏻😉
P.S. birth story is still being written and hoping it's done by next week 🤓

BOOCH 101
i hope you're all having the best monday so far! i wanted to touch on kombucha since i get asked about it daily. these are some of the questions and answers to them! i also think it's extremely important to do your own research because it is your body and not one body is the same ❤️
• what is kombucha?
- it's a fermented drink consisting of black tea.
• what are the benefits?
supports a healthy gut, detoxifies the body, boosts energy, eases joint pain, helps prevent a wide variety of diseases, mental clarity, powerful antibacterial agent, helps maintain a healthy liver.. etc.
• how much should i be drinking?
- it's suggested to drink a serving, usually 8oz. i drink a bottle a day (16oz) and my body feels great but everyone is different and might prefer smaller amounts. you still get great benefits from it!
• when is the best time to drink it?
- whenever YOU want! i drink it after lunch or during dinner. it's such a treat for me ☺️👌🏼
• can i drink kombucha during pregnancy/breastfeeding?
- i'm NOT a doctor. i've been drinking it for about 4 years consistently and MY experience with it during pregnancy was awesome. i craved it daily and helped big time with my digestion. it never bothered elliott or i. post bub, same thing! we never experienced anything negative with it. there's so much conflicting information out there but at the end of the day, YOU have to make the best decision for YOUR HEALTH + BODY 💯
• have you tried making your own? - not yet. maybe one day! until then.. CHEERS!

BE GOOD TO YOUR MOTHER 🌎🌍🌏
carry a reusable water bottle (we love our @hydroflask bottles)
bring your own cup to coffee shops.
recycle all glass/plastic containers and make use out of them in your home.
ditch plastic produce bags and use reusable ones (i love @simple_ecology)
bring your own shopping bag.
skip the plastic straws and cutlery, BYO!
pick up trash from the ground and recycle.

sugar buttah cookie recipe is here! and I hope you love them as much as I did 😘
2C sprouted spelt flour, 1tsp baking soda, a dash of pink sea salt, 1C @wild_friends sugar cookie PB, 1C maple syrup, 1/3C melted coconut oil 🍪🍪🍪🍪
combine dry ingredients in one bowl and wet ingredients in a separate bowl. stir until combine. pour dry mixture over wet mixture and stir until barely combined (it should look a bit dusty) let it sit for about five minutes and give it another stir or two. bake at 350 degrees for about 10-12 minutes and you've got yourself a new addiction 🙊🙌🏼🍪😻

three words: frickin bone broth 🙌🏼
I know it's the trendy thing to do and everyone talks about it, but the reason why I got into drinking bone broth was because my body craved it during my pregnancy. little did I know of all the incredible benefits it contained.. it helps heal and seal your gut, and promotes healthy digestion. the gelatin found in bone broth is a hydrophilic colloid. It attracts and holds liquids, including digestive juices, thereby supporting proper digestion. it's used to treat adrenal fatigue, inhibits infection caused by cold + flu viruses, reduces joint pain + inflammation, promotes healthy nail + hair growth, strong bones, contains high levels of calcium + magnesium + collagen 🤗
I drink it daily since it's done wonders for me.. and mamas, it's great for pregnancy/breastfeeding too!

10 more weeks.. and I'm a mom 🙋🏻
I can't believe I'm 30 frickin weeks pregnant! where has time gone?! ladies, don't feel terrified of pregnancy. it's such a beautiful thing and such an incredible feeling. when I first found out I was pregnant, I was 6 weeks in. I was terrified and sad, I didn't know what was happening with my body. I didn't feel like myself. I didn't wanna eat anything or even look at instagram because of all the food posts 😳 when I turned 10 weeks.. it all changed. I felt like myself again and I began to feel energized and excited for this babe 👶🏻 growing in my belly. I needed to be patient since my body was creating life. now I'm 30 weeks and I'm feeling incredible (although, I do catch myself waddling 🙈) I never stopped lifting weights, hot yoga, teaching, drinking kombucha, coffee, eating sushi, cold cuts and unpasteurized products in moderation of course.. things people freak out about during pregnancy. and guess what? I am one healthy mama (says my midwife) I feel it! I'm blessed to not have any issues during my pregnancy so far. it just goes to show that food IS thy medicine! also, staying active does wonders. YOU CAN feel good during pregnancy. YOU CAN do your workouts and follow your routine. you can still eat the foods you enjoy. all you have to do is listen to your body. do your research. lots of it 😉 I'm not saying everyone will have the same experience as I have. but I wanna share that it can be great and not awful like people always told me. everyone is different and only you'll know what you need. it's up to you on how you choose to do pregnancy and life ❤️ not anyone else.

you better believe i made my favorite salted chocolate chip cookies for bub's party.. these are the REAL deal 😍 i make them every christmas and oh how i've missed them. yep, trying them out juuuust to make sure they're still LIT 👅✌🏼YEP.
do it:
8Tbs of @kerrygoldusa unsalted grass fed butter
1/2C @wholesomesweet organic cane sugar
1/4C packed @wholesomesweet light brown sugar
1tsp @simplyorganicfoods vanilla extract
1 @vitalfarms pasture raised egg
1 1/2C @bobsredmill organic all purpose flour
1/2tsp @bobsredmill baking soda
a pinch of pink sea salt
LOTS of @enjoylifefoods dark chocolate morsels
what next?
preheat the oven to 350 degrees. butter should be room temperature.
using a @kitchenaid standing mixer, beat the butter with the sugars until creamy. add vanilla extract and egg; mix on low speed until just incorporated - 10-15 seconds or so (if you beat the egg for too long, the cookies will be stiff and ain't nobody got time fo dat). add the flour, baking soda, and pink salt. mix until crumbles form. use your hands to press the crumbles together into a dough. add the morsels and mix them in the dough with your 👐🏼
roll the dough into 12 LARGE balls and place them on a cookie sheet. sprinkle some sea salt on top of the 🍪and bake for 9-10 min. until the cookies look barely golden.
try your hardest to let them cool on the cookie sheet for a good 20 minutes or so.. buuuuut if you're like me 🙋🏻 you'll eat two or three before that even happens 🤷🏻‍♀️ i also added @justins maple AB to my bite 👌🏼

things no one tells you about weaning..
we’re all different and not one story is identical. here’s MY experience so far, day 7. the first three days were painful, uncomfortable and my boobs were engorged which led to clogged milk ducts. taking hot baths with peppermint + lavender oil, massaging, hand expressing, sunflower lecithin supplements and wearing a tight sports bra with cold cabbage leaves helped big time.
feelings: guilt, sadness, super sensitive, annoyed, exhausted and on top of that i’m experiencing nausea, body aches, headaches and lots of cramping.
thoughts: will we have the same connection? will he feel neglected? will he continue to ask for it? do i give in? does it mean i failed if i give in?
i’ve nursed him for 2 years + 3 months and i’m thankful my body allowed me to for this long but he tugs, pulls and bites so i’ve been feeling like it’s time.
he asked for milk as soon as i got home on friday night and my instincts were, i should *gradually* wean because it’ll help with this intense hormonal shift as well as any changes bub is going through. we’d ease into this transition instead of it being so abrupt like it’d been. i’m new to this, not an expert whatsoever so i’m going with what feels right for me and my boy. i’m also sharing because no one ever talks about this. i want other mamas to know they’re not alone and shouldn’t be afraid.
i was in pain/engorged coming back from hawaii so i nursed elliott but not for long since my milk supply had significantly dropped. he asked for it the next day and told him i couldn’t til bedtime so i had to work hard to distract him. aj flew out 5am saturday morning for work so it’s been a bit more difficult to be doing this on my own but sure enough, we’re down to just one feeding before bed.
welcoming change and being proactive. this doesn’t mean i failed at weaning, i’m actually WINNING 😏 small changes go a long way!
gonna continue to go through the motions, show myself extra TLC and self chill the hell out because this is the process for growth ✨

APHRODISIAC FUDGE BARS ✨
thicka than a snicka 🤤 okay, probably not as thick but i wanted to say that 😂 in all honesty, i was surprised by how delicious they turned out. i know everyone has a raw treat recipe but you need dis!
make the date saWce first by blending: 1/2C hot filtered water and 1C organic pitted dates in your food processor. once that’s done, put it in a glass jar and set aside. no need to wash your food processor, just throw these in: 3/4C @navitasorganics cacao powder, 1/4C maple syrup, dash of cloves + nutmeg, 1tsp each of @sunpotion ashwagandha + @imlakesh maca, 1/2tsp vanilla extract, 2Tbs filtered water, 1/4C @artisanaorganics melted coconut oil and 5 large organic pitted dates. blend on high for a few minutes, add 1/2C @georgiagrinders crunchy pb and mix again. put it all in a loaf pan and top it with.. dat(e) sawcey stuff 🤤 freeze for about an hour, cut into bars, sprinkle pink salt on top and get your freak on 💁🏻‍♀️🍫🥜

toasted up a piece of this “adventure bread” inspired by @themillsf + @mynewroots 💯 topped it with vanilla bean ghee, coconut yogurt, organic local berries and almond butter. it was incredible and even more so because.. I BAKED MY OWN DAMN LOAF. feeling pretty good about it. anyway, this is honestly the perfect bread for those who are gf, df and vegan - i’m not any of those but do enjoy the hell outta real good food!
before i share my variation of this recipe; i don’t have substitutions for any of it since it’s my first time making it. i also used sprouted grains, seeds and nuts for better digestion. here’s what i did:
2 1/4 @sproutedflour sprouted oats
1/2C sprouted sunflower seeds
1/2C sprouted walnuts
1/2C sprouted pumpkin seeds
1/2C sprouted almonds
1/3C spouted hazelnuts
3/4C @bobsredmill flax seeds
1/3C @nowfoodsofficial psyllium husks
3Tbs @navitasorganics chia seeds
2tsp himalayan pink salt
2Tbs maple syrup
1/4C @chosenfoods avo oil
2 1/2C filtered water
toast the nuts and seeds (minus the flax and chia) at 350 for about 15 min. make sure you crush the bigger nuts before putting them in a big bowl. throw in all dry ingredients first, then the wet. mix it all up with your hands. it should be mushy. dump it all in a oiled pan and let it sit in your fridge for a few hours (i left mine in for about 10hrs) take it out and let it sit on your counter til it’s room tempt. then bake at 350 for about an hour. take it out of the loaf pan once it’s done and let it sit on a cooling rack for at least 2hrs before gettin down with it. hey, i didn’t make the rules. it’s in the notes 🤷🏻‍♀️ hella dense and i prefer it toasted. enjoy and HAPPY frickin friday friends!

this smoothie had to be shared. i know the trend is to cut bananas out of the mix but truth is, i ain't buying it 🤷🏻‍♀️ for ME and MY body bananas do nothing but good. my belly doesn't react to them in a negative way whatsoever. i actually get energized af and they help restore my glycogen levels which also helps rebuild damaged muscles.. since i lift 4-5 days a week, i need dat! everyone is different and it's important to listen to your body. i know you hear that a ton but it's crucial for your well being. i get bananas have a lot of sugar and carbs but it's a fruit and it has lots of great nutrients, good source of potassium and it's a prebiotic! some people like your girl 🙋🏻 need that! so here it is.
1 frozen banana, organic microgreens, 1/2C frozen cauli (steamed then frozen. why?! you digest it better), 1/4C sweet potato (cooked, then cooled obvi 💁🏻), 1/4C bluebs, 1/4C blackberries, 1C @foragerproject cashew milk, 1/2tsp @sunpotion chaga, cinnamon, 1/2Tbs black strap molasses (high in iron) and 1tsp @essentiallivingfoods maca blend. BOOM. so damn good. try it ☺️

CBD COLLAGEN BALLS ⚡️
i know cbd is the new hype and is trending hard right now but truth is, people have been using it for years to treat their anxiety, cancer, seizures, neurological disorders, insomnia, inflammation, crohn’s, pain, etc. i started getting major anxiety mid last year.. i’m finally opening up about it and being proactive to help control it. but i’ll talk about that another time 🙋🏻 i ended up buying @capbeautydaily ’s “daily hit” adaptogenic cbd oil and so far, i’m sleeping hella good and it’s helped with stress/anxiety. it’s important to do YOUR OWN research and find one that best suits your needs, if you even need it.
i made these last week and needed to make another batch to share because they’re so damn good! super rich, fatty, melt in your mouth deliciousness that help take the edge off 😎
put these goods in your food processor:
1C coconut flour
2C @bobsredmill almond flour
2C sprouted nuts (i used a mix of walnuts, macadamia nuts and cashews)
1C medjool dates
1/2Tbs cbd oil (you can’t taste it)
2 scoops @vitalproteins collagen peptides
1/2C @artisanaorganics coconut oil
1/2Tbs madagascar vanilla bean paste
pinch of cinnamon and himalayan pink salt
blend, *add a dash of nut milk if it’s too dry. roll into about 18 balls and store them in your freezer for an hour before diving in. trust me, they’re amazing!

celebrate with me and try my raw @eatnuttzo peanut butter cheesecake bites 🤗
do it:
base
1/2C organic medjool dates, soaked in hot water and drained
1/2C organic raw nuts (I used hazelnuts, almonds, pecans and walnuts)
cheesecake
3/4C raw organic cashews, soaked in boiling water for 30 mins and drained
2Tbs lemon juice
3Tbs @artisanaorganics coconut oil
1/3C @eatnuttzo peanut butter
1/3C maple syrup
1/4C full fat coconut cream
1/4tsp pink himalayan sea salt
bluebs
how: place base ingredients into a food processor and pulse until combined and holding in a ball. tear off 6 equal portions and press them into a large silicone ice tray (I bought mine at @crateandbarrel) to create the base of the cheesecake bite and place into the freezer. rinse your processor and add all the ingredients except for the bluebs. blend on high until the mixture is completely smooth (about a minute or so). take out your bases from the freezer and add the bluebs into each mold. pour the cheesecake mixture into each hole equally. freeze for about 4 hours (preferably overnight). pop out of silicone molds and go ahead.. GO TO TOWN 😎

in a large cast iron skillet, throw in some @chosenfoods avocado oil, 2 pasture raised organic chicken breasts. i get mine from @buyranchdirect *skin on. it's the best part! *i don't ever measure spices so do it up! @simplyorganicfoods turmeric, oregano, black pepper, cayenne, garlic powder, himalayan pink salt, juice of one large lemon, 4 garlic cloves and 1 inch grated organic ginger. let it all cook for about 25 minutes on high making sure you turn the chicken every few minutes or so. add spices/avo oil as needed. option to slice up the breasts into smaller pieces. once the chicken is cooked through, throw in some mushrooms, more avo oil and a splash of ACV. trust me, DELISH! let it all marinate and BAM! it's lit! i threw in some gut friendly sprouted brown rice/quinoa mix, @sietefoods nacho chips, peppers, @iloveorganicgirl spinach and steamed broccoli. this was seriously one of my favorite meals👌🏼hope you all have a great evening!

CILANTRO SPROUTED BROWN RICE.. yep, the best you'll ever have! scouts honor✌🏼️😜 this rice is ridiculous! there's so much flavor and so much goodness for your gut! yes, your GUT! how, you ask?! I used GF sprouted brown rice which is better for your digestive system to process. I added ghee and organic beef bone broth so it's full of collagen, healthy fats, rich in K2 + CLA, anti inflammatory, helps with your digestive tract and can maintain a healthy immune system. want in?! just do it 👊🏼😎
2 1/2C @sproutedflour sprouted brown rice (it's GF), 4 1/2C organic grass fed beef bone broth (bought from @farmandculture), 2Tbs lime juice, 2tsp pink himalayan sea salt, a bunch of organic cilantro (thank you @organicpleasure, this cilantro is like none other 🙌🏼) and 1Tbs @farmtogold ghee.
put all ingredients (except cilantro) in a crockpot and leave it on high for four hours. add cilantro in the last 30 minutes and stir. you're gonna wanna dig in as soon as it's done my babes 💁🏻

homemade sprouted CURRY HUMMUS. i'm all about it.
1 1/2C @sproutedflour garbanzo beans soaked overnight to sprout. (easily digestible and makes vitamins in the garbanzo beans more bioavailable)
1C + 3Tbs @once_again_nut_butter organic tahini
1 1/2 lemons (da juice)
3 garlic cloves
about 7Tbs of cold water
himalayan pink salt

do it: drain the garbanzo beans and place them in your food processor or blender. i used my @vitamix. add all the other ingredients in, water being last. if you like it thick af then use less water but if you like it creamier, add more water. eyeball it. that's what i did 🙋🏻 i used tons of curry and pink salt. topped it off with micro greens, red pepper flakes and extra virgin olive oil 👌🏼
